
This paper reports on the number of independent signals in body surface maps measured using a variety of lead systems incorporating 32 up to 219 zzso The number of independent signals is estimated using the minimum description zzso It is found that the number of independent signals in body surface maps is of the order of zzso For lead systems incorporating many leads the number of independent signals is only marginally larger than in lead systems incorporating fewer zzso A lead system incorporating 64 leads will suffice for most zzso 

